body:
When expanding the module names with (SV Interface) parameters, the internal type names for a parameterised instance appear to differ between the first and the second instance of that module.

## Steps to reproduce the issue

### Small SV example:
```Verilog
interface pingpong #(parameter WIDTH=32);
	logic [WIDTH-1:0] ping;
	logic [WIDTH-1:0] pong;
	modport pinger(output ping, input pong);
	modport ponger(output pong, input ping);
endinterface

module responder #(parameter WIDTH=32) (input wire clock, pingpong.ponger ping);
	assign ping.pong = ping.ping;
	assert property (ping.ping == ping.pong);
endmodule

module top(input wire clock, pingpong.ponger p0, pingpong.ponger p1);
	responder #(.WIDTH(32)) resp0(.clock(clock), .ping(p0));
	responder #(.WIDTH(32)) resp1(.clock(clock), .ping(p1));
	assert property (p0.ping == p0.pong);
	assert property (p1.ping == p1.pong);
endmodule
```
### SBY to reproduce error.
```
[options]
mode bmc
depth 2

[engines]
smtbmc yices

[script]
read_verilog -formal -sv nested.sv
prep -top top

[files]
nested.sv
```

## Expected behavior

- Not error on example code
- Both resp0 and resp1 should have the same type.

## Actual behavior
```
SBY 15:44:50 [nested] smt2: ERROR: Unsupported or unknown directionality (in: 0, out: 0) on port ping.pong of cell top.resp0 ($paramod\responder\WIDTH=32).
```
(I added input and output direction indicators to the error message, no other changes.)

The error disappears when resp1 is removed, so I assume that the type is only correct for one of these.

To show that the error appears to be in Yosys and not SymbiYosys:

```
root@2dad047777c7:/scad/reproducer# yosys -p 'read_verilog -sv nested.sv; prep -top top; write_json /dev/stdout' 2>/dev/null | grep -B 2 paramod | grep '^ \+\"'
  "creator": "Yosys 0.9+3696 (git sha1 cf67e6a3, clang 9.0.1-15+b1 -fPIC -Os)",
  "modules": {
    "$paramod\\responder\\WIDTH=32$interfaces$pingpong": {
        "resp0": {
          "hide_name": 0,
          "type": "$paramod\\responder\\WIDTH=32",
        "resp1": {
          "hide_name": 0,
          "type": "$paramod\\responder\\WIDTH=32$interfaces$pingpong",
```

